(1499, 2, '2013-08-05 22:51:42', '2013-08-05 22:51:42', '<div id="RightRail" class="noborder">\r\n    <div class="video"><iframe width="224" height="152" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/vuz-LHp9Lzg?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\r\n<div class="space"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="leftContent">\r\n<h3><span>Partners.</span> We have over 100 TownWizard community guides, with more locations being added every week!</h3>\r\n<div class="rule"></div>\r\n<div class="phone">\r\n  <img alt="" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2013/samples/iphone.jpg" />\r\n  <div class="Screen"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="logos">\r\n    <a href="http://www.destinshines.com" target="_blank"><img alt="Destin Shines" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2013/samples/destin.jpg" /><h4>Destin, Florida</h4><h3>Darren Nelson</h3</a>\r\n    <a href="http://goudagenda.nl/" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2013/tiles/gouda.png" /><h4>Gouda, Netherlands</h4><h3>Peterpaul Kloosterman &amp;<br />Marcel van den Tooren</h3></a>\r\n<div class="space clear"></div>\r\n    <a href="http://www.charlottespotlight.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2013/tiles/charlotte.png" /><h4>Charlotte, North Carolina</h4><h3>Fabian Crespin</h3></a>\r\n    <a href="http://www.pcola.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2013/tiles/pcola.png" /><h4>Pensacola, Florida</h4><h3>Jay Brindley</h3></a>\r\n    <a href="http://bilbao.townwizard.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2013/tiles/bilbao.png" /><h4>Bilbao, Spain</h4><h3>David Rutges</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>', 'TownWizard Community Guides', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1138-revision-4', '', '', '2013-08-05 22:51:42', '2013-08-05 22:51:42', '', 1138, 'http://www.townwizarddev.com/1138-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1496, 2, '2013-08-05 20:51:36', '2013-08-05 20:51:36', '<div id="RightRail" class="nopad">\r\n    <div class="video"><iframe width="224" height="152" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/vuz-LHp9Lzg?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\r\n<div class="space"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="leftContent">\r\n<h3><span>Partners.</span> We have over 100 TownWizard community guides, with more locations being added every week!</h3>\r\n<div class="rule"></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="logos">\r\n    <div><h3>Selected Local Guides</h3></div>\r\n    <a href="http://www.ttowntoday.com" target="_blank"><img alt="TTown" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/ttown.jpg" /></a>\r\n    <a href="http://sociallifemerida.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="Grapes" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/sl.jpg" /></a>\r\n    <a href="http://www.gojoco.com" target="_blank"><img alt="Smiley" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/smiley.jpg" /></a>\r\n    <a href="http://www.cullmanlife.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="Cullman Life" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/cullman.jpg" /></a>\r\n    <a class="nomarg" href="http://www.802theapp.com" target="_blank"><img alt="802 The App" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/802.jpg" /></a>\r\n    <div class="space clear"></div>\r\n    <a href="http://www.pcola.com" target="_blank"><img alt="pcola" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/pcola.jpg" /></a>\r\n    <a href="http://thehaguemidtown.townwizard.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="Gouda Guida" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/hague.jpg" /></a>\r\n    <a href="http://www.30a.com" target="_blank"><img alt="30A" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/30a.jpg" /></a>\r\n    <a href="http://mylbilife.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="VB Compass" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/lbi.jpg" /></a>\r\n    <a class="nomarg" href="http://memphispop.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="Memphis Pop" src="/wp-content/themes/5506/images/2012/logos/memphispop.jpg" /></a>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n</div>', 'TownWizard Community Guides', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1138-revision-2', '', '', '2013-08-05 20:51:36', '2013-08-05 20:51:36', '', 1138, 'http://www.townwizarddev.com/1138-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1139, 1, '2011-01-12 09:24:13', '2011-01-12 09:24:13', '<div class="leftContent">\r\n\r\nHere''s a list of "Frequently Asked Questions" (FAQs). If you can''t find the answer to your questions here though, please don''t hesitate to call us toll-free now at 1-866-651-0001.\r\n<div id="faqs">\r\n<h3>Q: Can I customize my website and mobile apps?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nAbsolutely! You can choose your own logo and from a selection of color schemes. You can easily add, delete or edit content instantly for your guide using our templates.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: Can you view the guide on a tablet?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nYes. In fact, your website will be tablet-responsive for optimal viewing on an iPad or other tablet.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: So, is this a franchise?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nTownWizard and you are independent contractors. We provide the software, tools, resources, experience, cross-promotion and advertising opportunity to help you create, launch and sustain a new mobile guide.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: So, how do I make money?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nThere are many ways to make money from using TownWizard service, especially one as exciting as mobile computing, including ads, coupons, sponsorships, ecommerce, video and content distribution, branded merchandise, and more. The easiest to start with is ads. As the website and app you will be using becomes known as the #1 mobile guide to your community, advertisers will want to place their targeted message on your apps and website. As more and more people turn to you to learn where to dine locally and where to go for lively entertainment, advertisers will want to make sure that they stand out. We’ll provide you with sample ad sales kits and instructional videos on how to sell and place ads on the website and app.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: Do I need to form a company to use your product?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nNo, it’s certainly not a requirement to sign-up for our service. You should always discuss such matters with a tax and/or legal professional.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: How will people find out about my guide?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nBoth TownWizard and you are going to promote the website and app you will be using. Our partners have enjoyed excellent success using Google AdWords and Facebook ads, as well as viral marketing, social media and media trades. Because of the geographic nature of TownWizard, such online advertising campaigns can be very specific and very cost efficient. However, we’ve found that “word of mouth” works best in many locations. Our partners also participate in routine conference calls to share marketing ideas, ad rates and other useful info. It’s an outstanding way to learn what’s working in other communities. We also offer other tools to help you, such as press release announcement templates that you can quickly send out to local newspapers, radio stations, TV stations, etc.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: Can I charge users to download my app?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nNo, we do not permit people to charge for downloading the app. Get as many users as you can. Remove the barriers for people to download and use the app, and focus on getting market share so you can attract advertisers. One single ad placement could outweigh what you would charge for thousands of downloads.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: I''m not very good with computers.</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nWell, being good with software, Facebook, etc. will certainly make your life easier, but if you’re not the next Bill Gates, don’t worry. The Joomla CMS that we make available to you features very on-screen instructions and provides you with all you need to know to enter information about events, restaurants, bars and other “hot spots” in your area. Anyone can do it, if you’re willing to roll-up your sleeves and learn the CMS. Plus, we provide live orientation, ongoing training and tutorial videos that walk you through each process, step by step.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: If I purchase this product, who actually owns the app?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nTownWizard is a service. We own the software and other technology used in the apps and other services we provide (such as the website you will be using), apart from some third party software, such as the Joomla CMS, which is licensed to us; with certain exceptions, you and we will share ownership of the content. [Please see the Service Agreement for details.] .\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: Is your product only designed for small towns?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nNo, we are not limited to just small towns! Any hyper-local ‘community’ can have an app. We’ve partnered with large resorts who use the app as an on-site concierge and marketing tool. We’ve also partners with niche interest groups who share a common interest. Maybe you have a fishing enthusiast group in your community, or perhaps you want to create a mobile app that guides people to charming bed and breakfasts or kid-friendly parks in your town, the possibilities are endless!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: How much time will it take every day to manage my business?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nLike any new endeavors, the more time you invest in your new venture, the faster it will grow. It just depends on your personal goals and timeline. The content / editorial stuff is very easy. Anyone can manage that content with just a couple hours a day. The great news is, you can do your work from anywhere with internet access: at home in your slippers, at your favorite local hangout, or even from a boat or another country! This business is designed to be <strong>mobile.</strong>\r\nWe require you to regularly submit current, high quality content for inclusion into the website and app as well as fulfill your marketing obligations.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: Are there any other expenses?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nWe strongly recommend that you hire a professional graphic designer to create a powerful logo for you. We can recommend some great designers who will design something for you for a low flat fee. But otherwise, your only cost is the initial start-up charge and then the monthly service fee. Any other expenses (marketing, administrative, etc.) are entirely up to you and your business plan budget.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: What customer support do you provide?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nYou will find that the TownWizard software is easy to use once you get over the initial Joomla CMS learning curve, but we’re here to help answer any questions that you have.\r\nAll of our partners are given access to a special customer support website, with tons of information and resources. We will also provide guidance to you on the generation of a local ad sales effort and marketing campaign. We provide a robust support system for our partners. This includes live technical support, mentoring from other partners, regular calls with sales and marketing experts and video tutorials. In addition, partners share ideas through our Facebook group and regular conference calls.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: Can your mobile apps and Content Management System be integrated with my existing website?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nMost of the time, yes! Our apps can be integrated with existing websites for a nominal customization fee. Please call us at 1-866-651-0001.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: Will you be adding new features in the future?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nDEFINITELY! We are always updating our website and mobile apps with new features as technology evolves.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: What about competing apps that provide "local" information like Yelp and UrbanSpoon?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nWell, if you live in Manhattan, San Francisco or Chicago, those apps might be able to help you find some good local restaurants. But their information is notoriously useless when it comes to smaller markets and other lifestyle/entainment information. Why? Because they don’t know your town or neighborhood as well as an authentic local like you. They don’t know the secret little local hangouts. No one tells them when a restaurant closes, or who just changed up their menu, or who just changed owners. And those are just the dining secrets. Those big national brands certainly don’t know which spot features live jazz tonight and they don’t have any information about that great street party taking place near the park this weekend. You’ll always know your home and neighbors better than those guys, and because you’re an expert on your town, you’ll always have a competitive advantage over those more generic apps.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: Do you host the web site and mobile apps?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nYes! We provide all hosting. In addition, TownWizard will be responsible for securing all rights to the URL for the Website, including maintaining the registration for the URL with the TownWizard domain name registrar. [Please see TownWizard Service Agreement for details].\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Q: What happens if I decide to cancel my account?</h3>\r\n<div class="answer">\r\n\r\nThere’s no cancellation fee and you can cancel at any time 30 days advance notice to permit a smooth transition for those who have downloaded the Apps.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[\r\n 	$(document).ready(function() { 		$(''#faqs h3'').each(function() { 			var tis = $(this), state = false, answer = tis.next(''div'').hide().css(''height'',''auto'').slideUp(); 			tis.click(function() { 				state = !state; 				answer.slideToggle(state); 				tis.toggleClass(''active'',state); 			}); 		}); 	});\r\n// ]]></script>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'FAQs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'faq', '', '', '2013-09-21 17:31:05', '2013-09-21 17:31:05', '', 0, 'http://test.xhtmlchop.com/blog753/?page_id=13', 6, 'page', '', 0),
