(1534, 2, '2013-09-01 18:54:31', '2013-09-01 18:54:31', '<p align="center"><strong>CORPORATE SOLUTION LICENSE</strong><strong></strong></p>\r\nTHIS AGREEMENT (“AGREEMENT”), INCLUDING SCHEDULE A AND ANY ADDENDUM, CONTAINS THE ENTIRE AGREEMENT BETWEEN YOU (AND/OR THE BUSINESS THAT YOU REPRESENT) AND TOWNWIZARD, LLC (“TW”) WITH RESPECT TO YOUR USE OF THE TOWNWIZARD PLATFORM. READ THIS AGREEMENT CAREFULLY BEFORE YOU SIGN IT. BY SIGNING IT, YOU ACKNOWLEDGE THAT (1) YOU ARE AUTHORIZED TO EXECUTE THIS AGREEMENT ON BEHALF OF YOURSELF AND/OR THE BUSINESS YOU REPRESENT AND (2) YOU AND/OR THE BUSINESS THAT YOU REPRESENT AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THE TERMS OF THIS AGREEMENT IN THE COUNTRY FOR WHICH YOU REGISTER (“YOUR NOMINATED COUNTRY”). IF YOU DO NOT AGREE WITH THESE TERMS AND CONDITIONS, DO NOT SIGN IT AND THE PURCHASE WILL TERMINATE.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>A.  DEFINITIONS.  </strong>\r\n\r\nAs used in this Agreement:\r\n\r\n“<strong>Advertising Guidelines</strong>” means TW current guidelines for advertising and marketing websites and applications.  TW may amend the Advertising Guidelines from time to time in its sole discretion.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Advertising Revenue</strong>” means all gross revenue actually received by TW or You in a given month during the Term derived from advertising inserted into the Website, or into any Applications, or derived from interaction between the Website and another website(s) or Applications.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Applications</strong>” means applications targeted to the Website and Content that run on any destination device (such as a mobile device or tablet computer) receiving Content.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Approved Expenses</strong>” means third-party expenses associated with advertising and marketing of the Website and Applications which expenses are approved by TW and listed in the TW Advertising Guidelines.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Basic Support</strong>” means services supporting the launch of the Website and the Applications, minor bug fixes, ensuring Website availability, access to “how to” videos made generally available to its customers by TW, supporting business management documentation made generally available by TW to its customers and regular site backups.\r\n\r\n“<strong>CMS</strong>” means the content management system forming part of the Platform.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Content</strong>” means content contributed by TW or You to the Website and Applications developed for You as part of the Services and includes the text, software, scripts, graphics, photos, sounds, music, videos, audiovisual combinations, interactive features and other materials contributed to the Website and Applications.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Destination Areas</strong>” means the geographic area identified by You in this Agreement. In the United States, geographic areas are identified by the primary zip or postal code entered. The Destination Area will also include all contiguous zip or postal codes to the primary zip or postal code. In countries other than the United States, Destination Areas may be identified by a zip or postal code or similar geographic designation system if one exists, and if not, then by any reasonable means for clearly delineating a specific territory, including, but not limited to, references to roads or GPS coordinates.  Zip or postal codes or other similar geographic designation systems are not considered to be contiguous if they are separated by a body of water.  Notwithstanding the foregoing, the zip code 03874 will be considered part of the Destination Area for purposes of this Agreement.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Effective Date</strong>” means the date this Agreement becomes effective by Your signing of this Agreement.\r\n\r\n“<strong>End User” </strong>means a user of the Website or an Application provided as part of the Platform.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Fees</strong>” refers to the fees and payments that are due and payable by You to TW pursuant to Schedule A.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Governmental Authority</strong>” means any applicable federation, nation, state, sovereign or government, any federal, supranational, regional, state, local or municipal political subdivision, any governmental or administrative body, instrumentality, department or agency, or any court, administrative hearing body, arbitrator, commission or other similar dispute resolving panel or body, and any other entity exercising executive, legislative, judicial, regulatory, taxing or administrative functions of a government with jurisdiction over the applicable matter.\r\n\r\n<strong>"Intellectual Property Right" </strong>means any patent, copyright, trademark, domain name, moral right, trade secret right, or any other intellectual property right arising under any Laws and all ancillary and related rights, including all rights of registration and renewal and causes of action for violation, misappropriation or infringement of any of the foregoing.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Laws</strong>” means any laws, statutes, ordinances, codes, rules, regulations, published standards, permits, judgments, decrees, writs, injunctions, rulings, orders, administrative guidance and/or other requirements of any Governmental Authority.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Net Advertising Revenue</strong>” means Advertising Revenue less Sales Commissions and Approved Expenses.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Nominated Country</strong>” means the country for which You register in this Agreement.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Platform</strong>” means the TW Technology and Services enabling creation of mobile local guides.\r\n\r\n<strong>“Sales Commission”</strong> means the amount charged by either You or any Third Party Advertising Sales Representative for the active selling and collection of Advertising Revenue.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Services</strong>” means the services offered by TW as part of the Platform and included in the basic Fees, including, but not limited to access to and use of a Website, enablement and hosting services; content management system services; training and marketing services; Application development services.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Paid Services</strong>” means value added services that may be made available by TW to monetize the Website and Applications.  Paid Services are subject to fees and revenue shares and may be added or removed at the sole discretion of the TW.   TW will add or remove its offering of Paid Services by means of an Addendum to this Agreement.  The terms and conditions of the Addendum will be at TW’s sole discretion and such terms may be modified by TW from time to time at its discretion. Paid Services may include such things as Text Marketing, Email Marketing, Database Marketing, Social Media Management, Telemarketing sales of Local Advertising, Telemarketing Sales of National Advertising.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Taxes</strong>” means any and all sales, goods and services, use, excise, import, export, value added, consumption and other taxes and duties assessed, incurred or required to be collected or paid for any reason in connection with any advertisement, offer or sale of products by You on or through or in connection with the Services, or otherwise in connection with any action, inaction or omission of You or your affiliates or their respective employees, agents, contractors or representatives.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Technology</strong>” means the software applications, other intellectual property and know-how (including, without limitation, all techniques, know-how, algorithms, materials, specifications and source code related thereto) created and/or licensed by TW and utilized to provide the Services or otherwise included in the Platform, including, but not limited to all APIs, and any distinctive trade dress and trade styles (including, without limitation, color schemes), proprietary fonts, and the design, formatting, organization and structure of screens and other elements included within the Website and Applications, templates and coding; content management systems; bridges to content management systems;  Training and Marketing Materials.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Term</strong>” is defined in Section C(1).\r\n\r\n<strong>“Third Party Advertising Sales Representative</strong>” means a third party contracted by You or TW to assist with selling and collection of Advertising Revenue.\r\n\r\n<strong>“Third Party Materials</strong>” is defined in Section C(3)(c).\r\n\r\n“<strong>Trademark Usage Guidelines</strong>” means TW’s guidelines for usage of its trademarks, as such guidelines may be amended by TW from time to time in its sole discretion.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Training and Marketing Materials</strong>” means the videos, manuals, presentations and other resources that TW makes available to You to enable your use of the Platform.\r\n\r\n<strong>“TW Materials” </strong>means Content contributed by TW.\r\n\r\n“<strong>TW Trademarks</strong>” means the TW trademarks and service marks set forth in the TW Trademark Guidelines.\r\n\r\n“<strong>Website</strong>” means the website that is customized and provided by TW for your use as part of the Services.\r\n\r\n“<strong>You</strong>” and “<strong>Your</strong>” means you personally and the business, if any, that you represent.\r\n\r\n<strong>B.  <span style="text-decoration: underline;">ENROLLMENT</span></strong>\r\n\r\nTo begin the enrollment process, You must complete and sign this Agreement for the Services. Use of the Services is limited to parties that can lawfully enter into and form contracts under applicable law. As part of this Agreement, You must provide us with your (or your business'') legal name, address, phone number, e-mail address, Nominated Country and a Destination Area.\r\n\r\n<strong>C.  <span style="text-decoration: underline;">GENERAL TERMS</span></strong>\r\n\r\n1.  TERM\r\n\r\nThe term of this Agreement will start on the Effective Date and will continue until terminated by TW or You as provided below in Section 9 (the "<strong>Term</strong>").\r\n\r\n2. FEES AND TAXES\r\n\r\n(a) Fee details are fully described in Schedule A and may also be set forth in an Addendum to this Agreement. Unless otherwise agreed by TW and You in writing, all amounts contemplated in this Agreement will be expressed and displayed in US dollars, and all payments contemplated by this Agreement will be made in US dollars.\r\n\r\n(b) Fees are due and payable on a monthly basis in accordance with the relevant Schedule and/or Addendum.  TW reserves the right to impose, in which case You will pay, a late payment charge equal to the lesser of: (a) eighteen percent (18%) per annum or 1.5% per month, or (b) the maximum amount allowed by applicable law on any undisputed amounts that remain unpaid more than five (5) days beyond the due date.\r\n\r\n(c) As between the parties, You will be responsible for the collection and payment of any and all Taxes.  Any and all fees payable by you pursuant to this Agreement are exclusive of all sales, use and similar taxes, and you will pay any taxes that are imposed and payable on such amounts. You agree that TW is not obligated to determine whether Taxes apply, and that TW is not responsible to collect, report or remit any Taxes arising from any transaction contemplated by this Agreement.\r\n\r\n3.  YOUR OBLIGATIONS\r\n\r\n(a) In connection with Your use of the Services You will comply with all applicable Laws, and other requirements of any Governmental Authority that has jurisdiction over You.\r\n\r\n(b) You will be responsible for securing all rights to the URL for the Website, including maintaining the registration for the URL with a domain name registrar. You will comply with TW’s requirements regarding the URL and its administration with the registrar so that TW can provide the Services to You.  You will own the URL and all Intellectual Property Rights associated therewith.  TW may use your URL and brand in its offline promotion and website.\r\n\r\n(c) You must regularly submit current, high quality Content for inclusion into the Website and Applications. Your obligations relating to Content include the following:\r\n\r\nMaintain up-to-date, relevant Left Column content on the Website and Applications.\r\n\r\n- Maintain robust list of daily events.\r\n\r\n- Rotate and/or update event related photos weekly.\r\n\r\n- Add at least 1 new photo category with images at least monthly.\r\n\r\n- Add at least 1 new video to video category at least monthly.\r\n\r\nYou may not submit Content that is not specific or relevant to the Destination Area. You understand that TW does not guarantee any confidentiality with respect to any Content you submit.  You agree that: (i) Content you submit to the Service will not contain third party copyrighted material, or material that is subject to other third party Intellectual Property Rights (“<strong>Third Party Material</strong>”), unless You have permission from the rightful owner of the material or You are otherwise legally entitled to post the material and to grant TW all of the license rights granted herein and You have notified TW in writing that you are submitting Third Party Material; (ii) Content will not contain defamatory, obscene or other material which may be in breach of Laws; (ii) You will not transmit, distribute or store any Content in violation of any Law.\r\n\r\n(d) During the Term of this Agreement You agree not to distribute material or content that is similar to the Content on the Website or Applications to any competitor of TW.  You further agree not to promote, advertise, market, present or announce any content related to restaurants, events, or promotions outside the Destination Area.\r\n\r\n(e) You agree to comply with such policies as TW may implement from time to time concerning Destination Area Content, advertising, website design, or other matters relating to the use of the Platform.  You further agree to ensure that your Content is fresh and meets TW’s level of quality.  You acknowledge that TW may alter or remove Content contributed by You in TW’s sole discretion.\r\n\r\n(f) You acknowledge that TW will have no liability for any Content included in the Website and will have no liability for any of Your End Users’ claims relating to the Content or the Website.  You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold TW, its affiliates and licensors, and it and their respective employees, officers, directors, and representatives, harmless from and against all claims, damages, losses, liabilities, costs, and expenses (including attorneys’ fees) relating to (a) the Website or Applications or any Content that appears on the Website or Applications, including, but not limited to, (i) any claim that the Content infringes Intellectual Property Rights of any third party and (ii) any claim arising from the combination of the Website or Applications and the Content with other applications, content, or processes; (b) the use, development, design, manufacture, production, advertising, promotion, or marketing of the Website or Applications or any materials that appear on or within the Website or Applications; (c) your use of any Content, whether or not such use is authorized by or violates this Agreement; (d) Your violation of any term or condition of this Agreement; or (e) Your or Your employees'' negligence or willful misconduct.\r\n\r\n(g) You acknowledge that this is a non-exclusive agreement and that during the Term, TW may appoint other businesses who may operate websites in the Destination Area.\r\n\r\n(h) Both You and TW will have the right to market and promote the Website and the Applications.  You agree to use commercially reasonable efforts to promote the Website and Applications.      You have the right to place advertisements in the Website and/or Applications.  TW has the right to approve advertisements that You wish to place into the Website and/or Applications.  In doing so, you will comply with TW’s Advertising Guidelines.  You may not enter into any agreement with a Third Party Advertising Sales Representative that gives such third party the exclusive rights to market and/or advertise the Website or Applications, without prior permission from TW.  You acknowledge that TW may establish national accounts for advertisements or Destination Area content, and TW shall share revenue from such national accounts insofar as the revenue relates to Your Destination Area according to a policy to be determined from time to time by TW in its sole discretion.  As part of your marketing obligations, You agree to maximize the closing of credible sales opportunities and to provide reasonable support for the efforts of sales agents, including in the following core areas:\r\n\r\n- Regularly attend community events, festivals, meetings to promote the Website and Applications.\r\n\r\n- Actively utilize social media outlets such as Facebook &amp; Twitter with a minimum of at least 5 posts per week on each site.\r\n\r\n- Seek partnerships with other local businesses to offer giveaways and promotions.\r\n\r\n- Other non-required but highly encouraged marketing activities include the use of online pay-per-click advertising through Google, posters, postcards, promotional products and other advertising outlets\r\n\r\n- Print business cards\r\n\r\n- Develop a current Ad Rate Guide in electronic and print form.  TW will support the development of these documents.\r\n\r\n- Assist sales agent and TW sales and marketing consultants in the design and development of new collateral materials as needed.\r\n\r\n(i) You agree to use commercially reasonable efforts to provide TW with feedback and suggestions for improvement in relation to the Platform, the Website and the Applications.  If You or any of your affiliates elect to provide or make available suggestions, comments, ideas, improvements, or other feedback or materials to us in connection with or related to the Website, the Applications, or the Platform, TW will be free to use, disclose, reproduce, modify, license, transfer and otherwise distribute, and exploit any of the foregoing information or materials in any manner.\r\n\r\n(k)  During the Term of this Agreement and for a period of up to two (2) years after termination of this Agreement, You agree to provide TW or a third party nominated by TW will access to your records and accounts for the purpose of conducting audits with respect to Your compliance with the terms of this Agreement, including confirming compliance with Laws and confidentiality requirements.  Any such audits shall be conducted at TW’s expense.\r\n\r\n4.  INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY; RESERVATION OF RIGHTS\r\n\r\n(a) You acknowledge and agree that TW (or its licensors, as applicable) owns all Intellectual Property Rights in and to the TW Platform, the TW Materials, the Website, the Applications and the TW Trademarks, and, except as explicitly included in this Agreement, You do not, by virtue of this Agreement or otherwise, acquire any ownership interest, Intellectual Property Rights or other rights in or to the TW Platform, the TW Materials, any TW Trademarks, the Website, the Applications or any other intellectual property or technology that TW provides or uses in connection with the Services. All licenses not expressly granted in Agreement are reserved and no other licenses, immunity or rights, express or implied are granted by us, by implication, estoppels or otherwise.\r\n\r\n(b) You may not and may not authorize any other party to do the following to or with the Website, the Applications or the Platform: (i) reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble them; (ii) modify or create derivative works based upon them in whole or in part; (iii) distribute copies of them; (iv) remove any proprietary notices or labels on them; (v) use any Public Software in any manner that requires, pursuant to the license applicable to such Public Software, that the Platform, the Website, the Applications or any TW Materials be disclosed, licensed, distributed or otherwise made available to anyone; or (vi) resell, lease, rent, transfer, sublicense, or otherwise transfer rights to them. In addition to any other rights or remedies that TW may have, any use in violation of this section will immediately terminate your right to use the Website, the Applications, the Platform and the TW Materials.\r\n\r\n(c) You agree that when you contribute Content for inclusion into the Website, an undivided one-half interest in any such Content will automatically pass to TW at the time of contribution, unless such Content is Third Party Material, in which case, You automatically grant to TW a perpetual, non-exclusive, irrevocable, worldwide, assignable and sub-licensable, royalty free license to use, reproduce, perform, display, distribute, adapt, modify, re-format, create derivative works of, and otherwise commercially or non-commercially exploit in any manner, the Third Party Materials on the Website and in connection with the Platform.(d) Subject to Section 4(b) above and to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, TW grants You a limited, revocable, non-sub-licensable, non-assignable, non-exclusive and royalty-free license to access and use the Services, the CMS, the Website, the Applications and the TW Materials in the manner permitted by this Agreement.\r\n\r\n5. TRADEMARKS\r\n\r\n(a) Conditioned upon your compliance with the Trademark Usage Guidelines and the terms of this Agreement, TW grants you a non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-assignable, revocable right and license during the Term of this Agreement to use the TW Trademarks solely in connection with Your use of the Services. You must use the TW Trademarks solely in the manner in which they were provided to You, meaning you may not change, alter, amend, vary, or modify the TW Trademarks in any way, at any time. You may not sublicense these rights or otherwise permit any third party to use the TW Trademarks without TW’s prior written consent. You acknowledge that TW and its affiliates are the sole owners of the TW Trademarks, and You agree to do nothing inconsistent with that ownership. All goodwill arising out of Your use of the TW Trademarks will inure to the sole benefit of TW and its affiliates. TW may revoke Your license to any or all of the TW Trademarks at any time in its sole discretion. Upon the termination this Agreement, or termination or suspension of the Services, You shall immediately cease and discontinue all further use of the TW Trademarks.\r\n\r\n(b) Nothing in this Agreement grants to You the right to use any of the TW Trademarks or phonetically or confusingly similar terms, or a colorable imitation of the terms as all or part of a domain name. You agree not to directly or indirectly use, register or attempt to register anywhere in the world any domain name containing any of the TW Trademarks, or phonetically similar terms, or a colorable imitation of the terms as all or part of a domain name.\r\n\r\n6. CONFIDENTIALITY\r\n\r\n(a) You and TW agree that during the term of this Agreement, either of them (“the <strong>Disclosing</strong> <strong>Party</strong>”) may disclose to the other (“the <strong>Receiving Party</strong>”) confidential information regarding the Disclosing Party’s software, business, marketing, and other confidential proprietary information (collectively “<strong>Confidential Information</strong>”). You acknowledge that information relating to the Platform is TW’s Confidential Information.  The Receiving Party shall not disclose, the Disclosing Party’s Confidential Information, or any part thereof, to any other person or entity at any time, other than employees and representatives of the Receiving Party with a need to know, and only as necessary to participate in or discharge obligations under this Agreement or to comply with Laws.  Each of You and TW agree to take all reasonable measures to protect the Confidential Information of the other party against any use or disclosure that is not expressly permitted in this Agreement.  The obligations contained in this paragraph (a) shall not apply in the event and to the extent that the information becomes generally known to or available for use by the public other than by an act or omission of a party to this Agreement in violation of  the terms of this Agreement.\r\n\r\n(b) Each of You and TW agree and acknowledge that a breach this Section 6 will give rise to irreparable damage to the owner of the improperly disclosed Confidential Information, inadequately compensable in damages.  Accordingly, the Disclosing Party shall be entitled to injunctive relief against the breach or threatened breach, in addition to any other legal remedies which may be available.\r\n\r\n(c) Each of You and TW shall, upon the request of the other party or upon the termination or expiration of this Agreement, return or destroy all tangible copies of any Confidential Information of the other party in its possession, and shall further delete or destroy any copies of such Confidential Information stored in any computer memory or electronic storage device.\r\n\r\n(d) Notwithstanding any provision of this Section 6 or any other provision of this Agreement, in order to cooperate with governmental requests, to protect its systems and customers, or to ensure the integrity and operation of its business and systems, TW may access and disclose any information it considers necessary or appropriate, including but not limited to user contact details, IP addresses and traffic information, usage history and posted content.\r\n\r\n(e) This Section 6 survives the termination of this Agreement for 24 months.\r\n\r\n7. CHANGES TO THE PLATFORM\r\n\r\nYou acknowledge and agree that TW may, from time to time in its sole discretion, and without any liability to You or any third party, vary the Platform, its specifications or the scope of the Services or suspend some or all access to the Platform. If TW does make such material changes to the Platform, TW will provide You with notice of the changes as soon as reasonably possible.\r\n\r\n8.  TW SUPPORT\r\n\r\nIn consideration of your payment of the Fees set forth in Schedule A, TW agrees to provide You with Basic Support. As a part of the support, TW shall give You access to the CMS so that You can add Content to the Website.  TW will also provide guidance to You on the generation of a local ad sales effort and marketing campaign.  You have the right to request that TW provide additional support (“<strong>Premium Support</strong>”).  TW may, but is not obligated to, agree to provide such Premium Support on terms to be agreed by You and TW.\r\n\r\n9. TERMINATION OR SUSPENSION OF THIS AGREEMENT\r\n\r\n(a) At any time within thirty (30) days from the Effective Date TW may terminate this Agreement for any reason on notice to you.  In the event of such a termination, TW will refund all Fees paid by You.\r\n\r\n(b) Either You or TW may terminate this Agreement at any time and for any reason with thirty (30) days prior notice to the other party.\r\n\r\n(c) TW may terminate this Agreement or suspend the Services immediately if You breach any term of this Agreement and the breach is not cured within ten (10) days of TW’s notice to You.\r\n\r\n(d) If You terminate this Agreement pursuant to paragraph (b) above or TW terminates this Agreement pursuant to paragraph (c) above, You agree that all Content contributed by You will become the sole and exclusive property of TW.  You agree that automatically upon such termination, all Your right, title and interest in such Content will be assigned to TW and that You will take all actions and do all things necessary to give effect to such assignment.\r\n\r\n(e) If TW terminates this Agreement without cause pursuant to paragraph (b) above, then You and TW agree that You will retain an undivided one-half interest in any Content contributed by You and that either You or TW may use such Content without the duty to account to the other party\r\n\r\n(f) You hereby irrevocably appoint TW as Your attorney to execute and do any such instrument or thing for the purpose of giving effect to paragraph (d) of this Section 9.\r\n\r\n(g) On termination of this Agreement, You will promptly pay (but in no case later than 30 days following termination, any Fees that may be due and payable to TW up to the effective date of termination.\r\n\r\n(h) Upon any termination of this Agreement, all rights and obligations of the parties will be extinguished, except that the rights and obligations of the parties under Part A and Part C, Sections3(f), 3(i), 3(j), 3(k), 4(a) through (c), 6, 9 through 14 , together with any accrued but unpaid payment obligations of arising under this Agreement, will survive the termination of this Agreement. No termination of this Agreement will relieve either party for any liability for any breach of, or liability accruing under, this Agreement prior to the effective date of termination.\r\n\r\n10.  DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTIES\r\n\r\nTHE PLATFORM, INCLUDING THE SERVICES, TECHNOLOGY, THE APPLICATIONS AND WEBSITE, AND THE TW MATERIALS ARE PROVIDED “AS IS”.  TW EXPRESSLY DISCLAIMS (A) ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES REGARDING THIS AGREEMENT, THE PLATFORM, INCLUDING THE SERVICES, TECHNOLOGY, APPLICATIONS AND WEBSITE, THE TW MATERIALS OR THE TRANSACTIONS CONTEMPLATED HEREBY, INCLUDING ANY IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE OR NON-INFRINGEMENT; (B) IMPLIED WARRANTIES ARISING OUT OF COURSE OF DEALING, COURSE OF PERFORMANCE OR USAGE OF TRADE; AND (C) ANY OBLIGATION, LIABILITY, RIGHT, CLAIM OR REMEDY IN TORT, WHETHER OR NOT ARISING FROM TW’S NEGLIGENCE. TW DOES NOT WARRANT THAT THE FUNCTIONS CONTAINED IN THE PLATFORM, THE APPLICATIONS AND THE WEBSITE WILL MEET YOUR REQUIREMENTS OR BE AVAILABLE, TIMELY, SECURE, UNINTERRUPTED OR ERROR FREE, AND TW WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY SERVICE INTERRUPTIONS, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO SYSTEM FAILURES OR OTHER INTERRUPTIONS THAT MAY AFFECT THE RECEIPT, PROCESSING, ACCEPTANCE, COMPLETION OR SETTLEMENT OF ANY ACCESS TO THE WEBSITE, THE CONTENT OR TRANSACTIONS.\r\n\r\n11. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY\r\n\r\nIN NO EVENT SHALL TW BE LIABLE TO YOU OR ANY THIRD PARTY (WHETHER IN CONTRACT, WARRANTY, TORT (INCLUDING NEGLIGENCE, PRODUCT LIABILITY OR OTHER THEORY), INDEMNIFICATION OR OTHERWISE) FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, EXEMPLARY, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION DAMAGES FOR LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA OR USE, OR RECOUPMENT OF ANY INVESTMENT MADE BY YOU OR YOUR AFFILIATES,  ARISING OUT OF OR RELATING TO THIS AGREEMENT, EVEN IF TW HAS BEEN ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH COSTS OR DAMAGES. FURTHER, TW’S AGGREGATE LIABILITY ARISING OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT OR THE TRANSACTIONS CONTEMPLATED UNDER THIS AGREEMENT WILL NOT EXCEED AT ANY TIME THE TOTAL AMOUNTS DURING THE PRIOR TWELVE MONTHS PERIOD PAID BY YOU TO TW.\r\n\r\n12. FORCE MAJEURE\r\n\r\nNeither You nor TW shall be liable for any delay, failure of performance or equipment or loss if and to the extent caused by events beyond the reasonable control of the parties and that could not have been prevented by commercially reasonably measures (any such failure being referred to herein as an “<strong>Force Majeure Event</strong>”).  The party whose performance is affected by such Force Majeure Event will promptly notify the other party, giving details of the circumstances of such Force Majeure Event, and the obligations of the party giving such notice will be suspended to the extent caused by the Force Majeure Event and so long as the Force Majeure Event continues, and the time for performance of the affected obligation hereunder will be extended by the time of the delay caused by the Force Majeure Event.\r\n\r\n13.  RELATIONSHIP OF THE PARTIES\r\n\r\nYou and TW are independent contractors, and nothing in this Agreement will create any partnership, joint venture, agency, franchise, sales representative, or employment relationship between us. You will have no authority to make or accept any offers or representations on TW’s behalf. You will not make any statement, whether on the Website or Applications or otherwise, that would contradict anything in this Section 13. This Agreement will not create an exclusive relationship between You and TW. Nothing expressed or mentioned in or implied from this Agreement is intended or shall be construed to give to any person other than the parties hereto any legal or equitable right, remedy, or claim under or in respect to this Agreement. This Agreement and all of the representations, warranties, covenants, conditions, and provisions hereof are intended to be and are for the sole and exclusive benefit of TW, You and End Users. As between You and TW, You will be solely responsible for all obligations associated with the use of any third party service or feature that You permit TW to use on Your behalf, including compliance with any applicable terms of use.\r\n\r\n14. MISCELLANEOUS\r\n\r\n(a) Each party represents and warrants to the other that it has the requisite power and authority to enter into and carry out the terms of this Agreement. Each party warrants and represents that it is qualified to do business in all jurisdictions in which it does business.\r\n\r\n(b) The subject headings and captions of the paragraphs, sections, and subsections of this Agreement are included for purposes of convenience only and shall not affect the construction or interpretation of any of its provisions. This Agreement shall be construed in accordance with its plain meaning, and shall not be construed against the party that drafted it or provided it.\r\n\r\n(c) You may not assign this Agreement, whether by operation of law or otherwise, without TW’s prior written consent.  TW may assign this Agreement on notice to you.  Any change of control of a business that You represent for purposes of this Agreement will be deemed to be an assignment.  Subject to the previous sentence, this Agreement shall be binding on and shall inure to the benefit of the parties hereto and their respective legal representatives and permitted assigns.  Any assignment in breach of this paragraph (c) shall be void ab initio and of no effect.\r\n\r\n(d) All notices, offers, acceptances and other communications required or permitted under this Agreement shall be in writing signed by the party making the same and shall be deemed given on the date of delivery if: (i) delivered in person or (ii) sent by same day or overnight courier service, or (iii) if sent by certified or registered United States Mail, return receipt requested, postage and charges prepaid, and properly addressed as follows:\r\n\r\nTo TW: TownWizard, LLC\r\n\r\nc/o Northwest Registered Agent, LLC\r\n\r\n3111 W. Dr. MLK Blvd., STE 100-B180\r\n\r\nTampa, FL 33607\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo You:  at the address listed in this Agreement\r\n\r\nEither party hereto may change its address for notice, election, and other communication from time to time by notifying the other party of the new address in the manner provided for giving notice herein.\r\n\r\n(e) All exhibits, schedules, addendum and attachments to this Agreement are hereby incorporated by reference into this Agreement and are hereby made a part of this Agreement.  In the event of any inconsistency between these general terms and the terms of any exhibit, schedule and/or attachment, these general terms shall control.\r\n\r\n(f) Whenever possible, each provision of this Agreement shall be interpreted in such a manner as to be effective and valid under applicable law, but if any provision of this Agreement shall be deemed unlawful, void, or for any reason unenforceable, then that provision shall be deemed severable from these terms and conditions and shall not affect the validity and enforceability of any remaining provisions.\r\n\r\n(g) This Agreement may be executed in counterparts, via telecopy or original signatures, which when taken together, will be deemed to be one (1) original instrument.\r\n\r\n(h) This Agreement is to be construed in accordance with and governed by the internal laws of the State of New York, without giving effect to any choice of law rule that would cause the application of the laws of any jurisdiction other than the internal laws of the State of New York to the rights and duties of the parties.  Notwithstanding the foregoing, if any version of the Uniform Computer Information Transactions Act (UCITA) is enacted as part of the law of the aforementioned state, said statute shall not govern any aspect of this Agreement or any license granted hereunder, and instead the law as it existed prior to such enactment shall govern. The parties agree that the Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods shall not apply to this Agreement.  Any claims or actions regarding or arising out of this Agreement must be brought exclusively in a state or federal court of competent jurisdiction sitting in New York, New York and each party to this Agreement submits to the jurisdiction of such courts for the purposes of all legal actions and proceedings arising out of or relating to this Agreement. Each party waives, to the fullest extent permitted by law, any objection that it may now or later have to (i) the laying of venue of any legal action or proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement brought in any state or federal court sitting in the exclusive jurisdiction set forth above; and (ii) any claim that any action or proceeding brought in any such court has been brought in an inconvenient forum.\r\n\r\n(i) In the event of default hereunder by any party as to any duty, warranty, representation, or obligation owed to the other party, which default results in efforts by the non-defaulting party to remedy same (whether or not lawsuit is filed), the defaulting party shall pay, in addition to such other sum(s) as may be due, all costs and expenses of such efforts, including, but not limited to, reasonable attorneys’ fees for all Proceedings in connection therewith.\r\n\r\n(j) EACH OF YOU AND TW UNCONDITIONALLY AND IRREVOCABLY WAIVE THEIR RESPECTIVE RIGHTS TO A JURY TRIAL WITH RESPECT TO ANY CLAIM OR CAUSE OF ACTION BASED UPON OR ARISING OUT OF, DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, THIS AGREEMENT, ANY DEALINGS BETWEEN PARTIES RELATING TO THE SUBJECT MATTER HEREOF, AND/OR THE RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN PARTIES, WHICH WAIVER IS INTENDED TO INCLUDE, WITHOUT LIMITATION, CONTRACT CLAIMS, AND ALL OTHER COMMON LAW OR STATUTORY CLAIMS.\r\n\r\n(k) If Your Nominated Country is Canada, then it is the express wish of the parties that this Agreement and any exhibits, schedules or attachments thereto have been drafted in English. (The following is a French translation of the preceding sentence: Dans l’hypothèse où votre Pays d’Election est le Canada, il est de la volonté expresse des parties que le présent contrat et/ou tous les documents qui s’y rattachent soient rédigés en Anglais).\r\n\r\n(l) This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties pertaining to the subject matter contained in it and supersedes any previous or contemporaneous oral or written agreements, representations, and understandings. TW may amend any of the terms and conditions contained in this Agreement (including any of the Schedules) at any time and at its sole discretion. Any changes will be effective upon notice to You. No waiver of any of the provisions of this Agreement shall be deemed or shall constitute a waiver of any other provisions, whether or not similar, nor shall any waiver constitute a continuing waiver.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<p align="center">SCHEDULE “A”</p>\r\n<p align="center">FEES, REVENUE SHARE AND PAYMENT TERMS</p>\r\nA. SIGN-UP FEE\r\n\r\nYou agree to pay to TW a sign-up fee of <span style="text-decoration: underline;">$2,995</span> per Destination Area. Additional Destination Areas may be added only by the mutual consent of the parties. The Sign-up Fee must be paid at the time that You submit this Agreement.\r\n\r\nB. SUPPORT FEE\r\n\r\nYou agree to pay TW pay a monthly support fee of <span style="text-decoration: underline;">$299</span> per month per Destination Area. You will be required to establish your own developer account with Apple, and we will guide you through this process.  The first monthly support fee will be due and payable no later than thirty (30) days from the Effective Date.  Support fees for every month thereafter during will be due and payable no later than the end of each succeeding thirty (30) day period.\r\n\r\nC.  PAID SERVICES REVENUE SHARE.\r\n\r\nTW shall pay to you on a monthly basis pursuant to terms agreed by You and TW, fifty percent (50%) of net revenue for Paid Services provided to third parties that utilize the Website or Applications.\r\n\r\nD. FURTHER PAYMENT TERMS\r\n\r\n1.  Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, all payments shall be in U.S. dollars\r\n2. TW’s preference is that all Fees be paid by You using ACH or credit card payment mechanisms.  If You choose to remit Fees in any other way, the monthly Support Fees will be increased by four percent (4%).  If TW is unable to process the monthly charges, You will be responsible for establishing an alternative payment arrangement within five days and You agree to pay any resulting processing fees that may have occurred.  TW will charge, and You agree to pay, an additional administrative fee of $25 if charges are declined by Your bank or credit card processor and TW re-invoices You.\r\n3. All invoicing and other payment communications required or permitted under this Agreement shall be sent via e-mail to billing@townwizard.com', 'Business License Agreement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '186-revision-2', '', '', '2013-09-01 18:54:31', '2013-09-01 18:54:31', '', 186, 'http://www.townwizarddev.com/186-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
